## Note on eBPF Code Licensing

The eBPF programs in this project (files ending in `.bpf.c`) use the
`char LICENSE[] SEC("license") = "GPL";` declaration, which is required for
eBPF programs to be loaded into the Linux kernel. This is consistent with
the project's GPL v2 license.

---

## License Compatibility

All third-party licenses included in this project (MIT and BSD-2-Clause) are
permissive licenses that are compatible with GPL v2. This means:

- Code from these libraries can be included in GPL v2 projects
- The combined work is distributed under GPL v2
- Original copyright notices and license texts are preserved as required
